      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This collector-grade 2001 BMW M3 (E46) represents the pinnacle of analog performance. Under the hood, the S54 3.2L straight-six sings to an 8,000 RPM redline, managed by six individual throttle bodies and a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission. This example is mechanically flawless, featuring a reinforced rear subframe and a documented VANOS system refresh. The chassis dynamics are sharpened by a variable M differential lock and MacPherson strut front/multi-link rear suspension, maintaining factory-spec kinematics. With zero oxidation on the undercarriage and a pristine interior, this specimen delivers an unadulterated, high-compression driving experience that is truly show-quality.",
